<dl id="n54129r"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54129r">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54129r"> 129(r)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> kavya (poesis audible) <small>Orange</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n54129r"><li>FW 93.22 </li><li><a href="../../flex/d/lexd.htm#n54129r">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/d/l39d.htm#n54129r">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n54129r">MS BL 47476a-198</ms> </li><li>JJA 49:417 <a name="dd10" href="../../ff/fdra/dda.htm#dd10">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/d/dd10.htm#n54129r">Draft: I.4&sect;1.10</a>/2.10</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">6. J&apos;ai donn&eacute; ici m&ecirc;me (<cite>Mesures</cite>, 15 octobre 1935) une traduction comment&eacute;e de ce Ier chapitre du <i>N.&Ccedil;</i>. (<i>L&apos;origine du Th&eacute;&acirc;tre</i>). Le Th&eacute;&acirc;tre est dit &laquo;Po&eacute;sie visible&raquo;, par distinction de la &laquo;<mark>Po&eacute;sie audible</mark> <font color="green">[seulement]</font>&raquo;, &agrave; laquelle j&apos;ai limit&eacute; la pr&eacute;sente &eacute;tude. <mark><i>K&acirc;vya</i></mark> &laquo;po&eacute;sie&raquo;, <i>kavi</i> &laquo;po&egrave;te &laquo;signifient aussi &laquo;sagesse, sage&raquo;, de la racine <i>ku</i>, <i>kav</i> &laquo;chanter&raquo;, ou de <i>k&ucirc;</i> &laquo;diriger sa pens&eacute;e &raquo;. <br><font color="green">[I have given here (<cite>Mesures</cite>, October 15, 1935) a translation and commentary of this 1st chapter of <i>N.&Ccedil;</i>. (<i>L&apos;origine du Th&eacute;&acirc;tre</i>). The Theater is said to be "Visible Poetry", by distinction from "Audible Poetry [only]</font>", to which I have limited this study. <i>K&acirc;vya</i> "poetry", <i>kavi</i> "poet" also mean "wisdom, sage", from the root <i>ku</i>, <i>kav</i> "to sing", or <i>k&ucirc;</i> "to direct one&apos;s thought".] <small> Ren&eacute; Daumal, <a name="RDLP" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#RDLP"><cite title="source">Les pouvoirs de la parole</cite></a> (1938) [83]</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
